1
00:00:31,490 --> 00:00:33,284
What's up?

2
00:00:34,535 --> 00:00:36,370
Great view.

3
00:00:38,206 --> 00:00:40,208
The harbor, I mean.

4
00:00:43,294 --> 00:00:46,380
It's fucking picturesque is what it is.

5
00:00:46,464 --> 00:00:51,385
I always ask myself, "is today the day I drive
to fort armistead to stare at the harbor?"

6
00:00:51,469 --> 00:00:57,099
No, I figure if I mind my own business, frank
will call and wake me at seven in the morning

7
00:00:57,183 --> 00:01:02,188
and tell me to get my ass down there
for some mysterious fucking reason so, hey.

8
00:01:08,486 --> 00:01:12,490
Good Anchorage, good cranes,
good railroads, close to i-95.

9
00:01:12,573 --> 00:01:14,200
Lot of people ready to work.

10
00:01:14,283 --> 00:01:16,285
That's my fucking town.

11
00:01:17,787 --> 00:01:21,749
Except we're another 110 miles
for any ship coming up from Hampton roads.

12
00:01:21,832 --> 00:01:24,460
An extra day. So why come, right?

13
00:01:24,543 --> 00:01:29,090
Unless you know your cargo's
gonna move fast and clean through the port.

14
00:01:29,173 --> 00:01:33,719
Why offload in Baltimore except that we can
turn your ship around faster than other ports?

15
00:01:33,803 --> 00:01:40,226
A Baltimore gang will make sure your cargo -
all your cargo - gets where it needs to go.

16
00:01:40,309 --> 00:01:46,274
- Like you never stole nothing back in the day.
- We ain't back in the day, Nicky.

17
00:01:46,357 --> 00:01:50,361
When did you last see trucks backed up
for three miles outside the terminal?

18
00:01:50,444 --> 00:01:55,533
If it wasn't for the car-ships, we'd
be starving. The cameras come back.

19
00:01:56,867 --> 00:02:01,455
I'm serious. They come back today. We tell
the shipper we lost the can in the stacks.

20
00:02:01,539 --> 00:02:04,542
They're gone. We turned them over already.

21
00:02:08,129 --> 00:02:10,131
To who?

22
00:02:11,882 --> 00:02:15,636
Patapsco line's a cunt hair away
from taking their business to Norfolk.

23
00:02:15,720 --> 00:02:18,806
- I don't need this shit.
- I do, uncle frank. I need the money.

24
00:02:18,889 --> 00:02:24,145
- God damn it! You ain't hearing me!
- You think this shit is fucking easy?

25
00:02:24,228 --> 00:02:28,441
Try living on five or six days a month.
See how fast it puts you on your ass.

26
00:02:28,524 --> 00:02:31,652
- I am on my ass, uncle frank.
- You need money, come to me.

27
00:02:31,736 --> 00:02:34,822
Frankie sobotka's
father fucking Christmas lately.

28
00:02:34,905 --> 00:02:39,452
- No doubt his pockets are full.
- You think it's for me?

29
00:02:39,535 --> 00:02:43,331
Is that what you think, huh?
It ain't about me, Nick!

30
00:02:45,791 --> 00:02:47,752
I know, I'm sorry.

31
00:02:47,835 --> 00:02:51,714
You got Ziggy mixed up in this?
Jesus, what the fuck are you thinking?

32
00:02:54,717 --> 00:02:58,471
Me and zig are gonna talk on this
long and hard.

33
00:03:12,193 --> 00:03:14,195
Let's go to work.

34
00:03:15,196 --> 00:03:18,366
- How much?
- Twenty.

35
00:03:18,449 --> 00:03:22,203
- Three-way split.
- Yeah? Who's the inside man?

36
00:03:23,537 --> 00:03:26,165
You don't know?

37
00:03:26,248 --> 00:03:28,751
Fuck you, then, I ain't no snitch.

38
00:03:30,878 --> 00:03:34,882
Nobody should flash too much money.
You know that much, right?

39
00:03:35,966 --> 00:03:37,259
Yeah.

40
00:03:43,682 --> 00:03:46,018
When you walk through the garden

41
00:03:47,353 --> 00:03:49,980
you gotta watch your back

42
00:03:51,565 --> 00:03:54,318
well, I beg your pardon

43
00:03:54,985 --> 00:03:57,988
walk the straight and narrow track

44
00:03:59,824 --> 00:04:01,909
if you walk with Jesus

45
00:04:03,035 --> 00:04:05,413
he's gonna save your soul

46
00:04:06,831 --> 00:04:08,999
you gotta keep the devil

47
00:04:09,834 --> 00:04:12,503
way down in the hole

48
00:04:14,255 --> 00:04:16,507
he's got the fire and the fury

49
00:04:17,883 --> 00:04:20,678
at his command

50
00:04:21,679 --> 00:04:24,515
well, you don't have to worry

51
00:04:25,391 --> 00:04:28,894
if you hold on to Jesus' hand

52
00:04:29,728 --> 00:04:32,481
we'll all be safe from Satan

53
00:04:33,524 --> 00:04:35,818
when the thunder rolls

54
00:04:36,694 --> 00:04:39,697
we just gotta keep the devil

55
00:04:40,531 --> 00:04:44,076
way down in the hole

56
00:04:52,543 --> 00:04:54,628
Down in the hole

57
00:04:56,672 --> 00:04:57,715
down in the hole

58
00:04:59,383 --> 00:05:02,553
you gotta help me keep the devil

59
00:05:03,512 --> 00:05:04,555
down in the hole

60
00:05:13,731 --> 00:05:19,153
Toxicology's coming back positive for
strychnine. 10%, 12%. It's pretty well laced.

61
00:05:19,236 --> 00:05:21,989
- This was intentional?
- That's the me's call.

62
00:05:22,072 --> 00:05:25,993
I've seen street packages cut all the time
with all kind of chemicals.

63
00:05:26,076 --> 00:05:28,829
Don't use too much,
you give a weak package some kick.

64
00:05:29,038 --> 00:05:34,335
People think you're high-grade when you got
stepped-on trash with rat poison mixed in.

65
00:05:34,418 --> 00:05:36,879
Too much poison, you
got people falling out.

66
00:05:36,962 --> 00:05:39,340
Be nice to have some answers for reporters.

67
00:05:39,423 --> 00:05:43,219
- What do they wanna know?
- How it got in, what we're doing, the usual.

68
00:05:43,302 --> 00:05:48,015
- It got in like everything gets in.
- If you can't win the war on drugs in a prison,

69
00:05:48,098 --> 00:05:50,059
where the hell you gonna win it?

70
00:05:50,142 --> 00:05:52,686
If it were one or two dead, it would fade.

71
00:05:52,770 --> 00:05:57,066
Five in one night, eight more in the
infirmary? We need to show the flag on this.

72
00:05:57,149 --> 00:06:01,153
- I need for y'all to wheel and deal.
- What do you mean?

73
00:06:01,237 --> 00:06:03,405
This case gets made from an informant

74
00:06:03,489 --> 00:06:08,035
and you'll have a couple dozen of them
if you're ready to shave some years.

75
00:06:15,292 --> 00:06:16,877
Colonel.

76
00:06:23,884 --> 00:06:25,719
- Jimmy.
- Winona.

77
00:06:28,764 --> 00:06:32,726
Hey, hey, hey. Gilligan, little buddy.

78
00:06:32,810 --> 00:06:34,812
Hey, don't you have a job?

79
00:06:35,729 --> 00:06:38,023
Ooh. Ouch!

80
00:06:44,446 --> 00:06:48,534
I smell fresh police
work. Ok, be like that.

81
00:06:50,578 --> 00:06:54,540
You got some paper from inside the can?
A letter, envelopes, scraps of stuff?

82
00:06:54,623 --> 00:06:57,251
Yeah, everything's in evidence control.

83
00:06:57,334 --> 00:07:00,337
- You got the submission slips?
- He does.

84
00:07:06,552 --> 00:07:09,263
- Lester.
- You want to pull all of it?

85
00:07:09,346 --> 00:07:11,473
Hold it.

86
00:07:11,557 --> 00:07:13,601
Before you start dancing
with your Jane Doe,

87
00:07:13,684 --> 00:07:16,770
I'll need something from you
on the gant case.

88
00:07:16,854 --> 00:07:20,274
I got a set of ilene Nathan's teeth marks
on my hind parts.

89
00:07:20,357 --> 00:07:22,568
- No problem.
- You found Omar?

90
00:07:22,651 --> 00:07:24,903
I never lost him, my friend.

91
00:07:28,490 --> 00:07:31,452
- He's got Omar?
- Bullshit.

92
00:07:31,952 --> 00:07:33,287
Who's Omar?

93
00:07:45,591 --> 00:07:47,968
My papers are in.

94
00:07:48,719 --> 00:07:50,179
They are.

95
00:07:50,262 --> 00:07:52,848
You want out, you're out.

96
00:07:54,558 --> 00:07:59,605
But I'm offering to clean the slate here.
You and me.

97
00:08:01,273 --> 00:08:04,985
Council vote is next week,
after which I'm upstairs.

98
00:08:05,069 --> 00:08:09,490
If I'm gonna give myself a chance to make my
Mark on this place, I'll need good people.

99
00:08:11,075 --> 00:08:13,077
People you can trust.

100
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:15,287
And you ain't that, hm?

101
00:08:16,080 --> 00:08:21,835
All right, you're a snake
but you seem to know your business.

102
00:08:22,419 --> 00:08:24,713
I'm taking the bar exam in a month.

103
00:08:25,214 --> 00:08:30,636
Why not put it off for a year or two, leave
the department with a major's pension?

104
00:08:30,969 --> 00:08:33,889
Scalise is gonna retire this summer.

105
00:08:33,972 --> 00:08:38,769
Do me a good turn on this detail in the
southeast and you'll have that posting.

106
00:08:39,436 --> 00:08:43,440
- Why would you do that?
- I value you, Cedric.

107
00:08:44,191 --> 00:08:47,903
Look, you're arrogant and disonal

108
00:08:47,986 --> 00:08:51,949
but maybe, given time,
you'll find a way to shine.

109
00:08:52,616 --> 00:08:55,744
- What's the detail?
- Drug case probably.

110
00:08:55,828 --> 00:08:59,123
My sense of it is that
valchek has got some personal issues

111
00:08:59,206 --> 00:09:01,542
with somebody in one of the port unions.

112
00:09:01,625 --> 00:09:07,423
He thinks they got too much money and so,
being valchek, he gets a detail.

113
00:09:07,506 --> 00:09:12,261
- That it? Pretty thin.
- I don't care if you make a case for valchek.

114
00:09:12,886 --> 00:09:17,808
I do care that the old polack comes away
from it feeling he got his money's worth.

115
00:09:20,144 --> 00:09:22,271
Valchek asked for me by name, didn't he?

116
00:09:23,439 --> 00:09:27,192
You two are trading horses
and you need me in the corral.

117
00:09:33,699 --> 00:09:35,284
How about this?

118
00:09:37,119 --> 00:09:39,204
If I bring in a case,

119
00:09:39,288 --> 00:09:43,917
you make the detail permanent
as a major case unit within cid.

120
00:09:44,001 --> 00:09:46,879
Fair enough. Just keep valchek stroked

121
00:09:46,962 --> 00:09:49,131
and make sure you bring in
a drug case or two.

122
00:09:49,506 --> 00:09:50,591
One other thing.

123
00:09:50,674 --> 00:09:53,844
A promotion and a specialized unit
isn't enough?

124
00:09:54,428 --> 00:09:56,472
I choose my own people.

125
00:09:58,182 --> 00:10:01,560
Fuck me once, shame on you.
Fuck me twice...

126
00:10:01,643 --> 00:10:06,648
Make a list. Give it to rawls.
He'll pull who you want.

127
00:10:21,914 --> 00:10:26,460
Shit do not make sense. Some of them
woulda got nothing. Tae? Lizard?

128
00:10:26,543 --> 00:10:30,506
Shit, if it was a hotshot, they was after
some real lightweight motherfucks.

129
00:10:30,589 --> 00:10:35,636
Yo, Dee, you want any silver surfers?
They tossing shit tae had in his cell.

130
00:10:39,348 --> 00:10:42,017
Whoever load that shit up ain't know
what he was doing.

131
00:10:42,100 --> 00:10:45,896
My boy down the infirmary say the shit
was more rat poison than it was dope.

132
00:11:02,621 --> 00:11:04,790
Fucking a, right?

133
00:11:16,677 --> 00:11:18,679
Jane Doe no.5.

134
00:11:22,975 --> 00:11:24,101
Five... five...

135
00:11:38,615 --> 00:11:40,617
What's up, baby?

136
00:11:44,454 --> 00:11:46,081
Ha-ha-hoo!

137
00:11:46,164 --> 00:11:48,500
Not here. Put it away.

138
00:11:48,584 --> 00:11:50,335
Shot and a beer, darlin'.

139
00:11:52,880 --> 00:11:57,217
- Kept one for yourself, did you?
- Them japs make a nice little camera.

140
00:11:57,301 --> 00:12:01,179
- You even got film in that bitch?
- No, it's digital.

141
00:12:01,263 --> 00:12:05,142
- I know it's digital, so what?
- So, no film, look.

142
00:12:05,225 --> 00:12:09,146
There's a computer chip inside.
You load the pictures onto the computer.

143
00:12:09,229 --> 00:12:11,315
Thanks, dolo.

144
00:12:12,107 --> 00:12:13,734
Hey, zig.

145
00:12:14,151 --> 00:12:15,986
Ziggy.

146
00:12:16,778 --> 00:12:18,697
Don't spread no cash
around for a while, ok?

147
00:12:19,406 --> 00:12:20,908
Hell, no.

148
00:12:20,991 --> 00:12:24,995
I mean, I might get a new clutch plate
put in Princess is all.

149
00:12:25,495 --> 00:12:28,707
- Also your father knows.
- How does he know?

150
00:12:28,832 --> 00:12:30,834
Horse saw us, right?

151
00:12:33,503 --> 00:12:36,590
- Fuck me. He told?
- How long's horse been tight with your pop?

152
00:12:36,673 --> 00:12:38,383
Of course he told.

153
00:12:38,967 --> 00:12:44,181
- He's pissed, zig. He ain't happy.
- What did you say?

154
00:12:46,141 --> 00:12:51,146
I told him we already turned the cameras
around and, after a while, he stopped yelling.

155
00:12:51,229 --> 00:12:54,149
Yeah, at you, maybe. Fuck!

156
00:12:55,400 --> 00:12:57,486
Anyway...

157
00:12:57,569 --> 00:13:00,989
- It's low profile for a while, all right?
- All right.

158
00:13:07,579 --> 00:13:11,625
You don't have to take a picture
to no photomart to get it turned around?

159
00:13:11,708 --> 00:13:13,877
No, it goes on a computer.

160
00:13:20,384 --> 00:13:22,386
I gotta take a leak.

161
00:13:47,077 --> 00:13:51,206
Ho! Pretty boy, hey, there!

162
00:13:51,915 --> 00:13:54,126
Oh, Christ, Ziggy.

163
00:14:01,550 --> 00:14:03,552
Jimmy, just a scheduling thing.

164
00:14:03,635 --> 00:14:08,932
Sean was invited to Mark's birthday party
on Saturday. Pick him up there after two.

165
00:14:09,016 --> 00:14:13,979
I realize it's your weekend but Sean would
be upset if he missed it. Ok? Great.

166
00:14:15,147 --> 00:14:19,109
Omar by the end of the week,
Jimmy. Ilene is on the warpath.

167
00:14:19,192 --> 00:14:21,319
Motherfucker, I am serious.

168
00:14:22,612 --> 00:14:25,198
Mr. Mcnulty,
this is Dr. Halpern's office.

169
00:14:25,282 --> 00:14:28,493
You missed your cleaning on Tuesday.
We haven't heard from you.

170
00:14:28,577 --> 00:14:29,703
Give us a call, please.

171
00:14:31,121 --> 00:14:33,540
Mcnulty, this is your
dear friend ilene Nathan.

172
00:14:33,623 --> 00:14:37,669
I indicted this piece-of-shit case
because you swore we had an eyeball wit...

173
00:14:48,388 --> 00:14:51,558
Drive time is 6.38am
and we have reports...

174
00:15:07,574 --> 00:15:11,411
- Go around, asshole.
- What did you call me?

175
00:15:11,495 --> 00:15:15,165
I'm sleeping on this side.
Cos you gotta get up, everybody does.

176
00:15:19,503 --> 00:15:21,296
Yup.

177
00:15:29,179 --> 00:15:31,848
Wipe off the seat, Nick, I know you hit it.

178
00:15:37,395 --> 00:15:41,316
- If I could fart now, I would.
- That's a surprise.

179
00:15:44,361 --> 00:15:46,613
No chance for breakfast, huh?

180
00:15:46,696 --> 00:15:48,865
No. I'll stop by the bar.

181
00:15:49,032 --> 00:15:53,453
No, you won't. You ain't got time. You
gotta run me past my ma's to pick up Ashley.

182
00:15:53,537 --> 00:15:56,289
Hurry up.
You know I got a ship to work today.

183
00:15:57,541 --> 00:16:00,252
Your ma knows you got a ship, too.

184
00:16:01,795 --> 00:16:06,591
Don't go upstairs. Just head out the back.
I'll pick you up in the back of the alley.

185
00:16:06,675 --> 00:16:08,677
Ow!

186
00:16:09,636 --> 00:16:15,100
We got a kid together. What's the big deal if
we spend the night in your folks' basement?

187
00:16:15,183 --> 00:16:17,185
They're decent people.

188
00:16:29,406 --> 00:16:32,159
- We ain't got time.
- I know.

189
00:16:32,242 --> 00:16:36,413
- So why are you grabbing?
- They were staring right at me.

190
00:16:49,634 --> 00:16:51,636
I'll meet you out back.

191
00:16:53,847 --> 00:16:57,434
So how do you get the
container off the ship, off the dock?

192
00:16:57,517 --> 00:17:02,355
To make sure your cargo isn't messed with,
you'd wanna get with one of the checkers.

193
00:17:02,439 --> 00:17:05,192
- Who are they?
- Local 1514.

194
00:17:05,275 --> 00:17:09,821
They monitor all the loading and offloading,
they match the manifests, tally the cargo.

195
00:17:09,905 --> 00:17:12,866
Nothing moves
without them putting it down somewhere.

196
00:17:12,949 --> 00:17:15,452
- Or not.
- Or not.

197
00:17:15,535 --> 00:17:18,121
So we need to talk to a checker.

198
00:17:18,205 --> 00:17:19,497
What?

199
00:17:19,581 --> 00:17:24,711
Black, white, Polish, Irish, Italian,
it doesn't matter. No one talks to police.

200
00:17:25,629 --> 00:17:27,631
How do you make a case, then?

201
00:17:29,299 --> 00:17:32,636
I patrol. I write traffic tickets.

202
00:17:32,719 --> 00:17:37,349
They got an open container
or a damaged container, I take a report.

203
00:17:37,432 --> 00:17:39,559
Something stolen, I take another report.

204
00:17:39,643 --> 00:17:45,232
If someone gets something dropped on 'em or
gets run over by a loader, I keep writing.

205
00:17:45,315 --> 00:17:47,776
That's the job, huh?

206
00:17:48,944 --> 00:17:52,113
- How long you been on?
- Two years.

207
00:17:52,197 --> 00:17:55,116
What did you do before that?

208
00:17:55,200 --> 00:18:01,915
I took tolls at the fort McHenry tunnel which,
I'm happy to say, wasn't nearly as much fun.

209
00:18:01,998 --> 00:18:06,419
Made 22,500, went home tired every night
till iwalked by the office bulletin board

210
00:18:06,503 --> 00:18:08,421
and read the mdotjob posting.

211
00:18:08,505 --> 00:18:13,218
Port authority officers, schedule one,
starting at 33 with benefits.

212
00:18:14,386 --> 00:18:16,805
Toll-taking days were over, huh?

213
00:18:19,557 --> 00:18:25,313
Father of my two kids went to Houston in
'99, hasn't so much as called in three years.

214
00:18:25,397 --> 00:18:30,026
I wasn't gonna make it on 22,500.
Not with kids, iwasn't.

215
00:18:31,361 --> 00:18:33,530
Did you want to be a police?

216
00:18:57,762 --> 00:19:01,391
- Could've been me the other night.
- Tme

217
00:19:01,474 --> 00:19:07,022
except you up and tell me to stop doing
that. Avon to the rescue. How did you know?

218
00:19:07,564 --> 00:19:12,027
I figured your ass was here to thank me
for pulling you off of that shit.

219
00:19:12,110 --> 00:19:16,364
Five dead, more in the infirmary.
How did you know?

220
00:19:16,448 --> 00:19:21,161
I did as your uncle should cos I'm
concerned about you fucking yourself up.

221
00:19:22,245 --> 00:19:24,205
You knew.

222
00:19:24,289 --> 00:19:29,294
Look, man, I ain't had nothing to do with
it. I mean... I might know who did, though.

223
00:19:29,377 --> 00:19:33,089
You practically running this place.
Who else could it be?

224
00:19:33,173 --> 00:19:36,676
It ain't about what happened,
you understand?

225
00:19:36,760 --> 00:19:40,055
It's about using what happened
to our advantage.

226
00:19:40,138 --> 00:19:45,268
- Play or you gonna get played.
- I need to know that you ain't do that shit.

227
00:19:45,352 --> 00:19:48,688
I already said it.
You ain't gonna believe it, fuck it.

228
00:19:48,772 --> 00:19:52,734
You can tell yourself I spiked it
but be grateful that you still standing.

229
00:19:52,817 --> 00:19:57,197
Once you done that, we can talk about
how to shave some of these years off.

230
00:19:57,280 --> 00:20:02,202
Not just for me, for you, too. They're looking
